+# Handoff: Add calendar events/meetings (model, calendar render, panel „Wydarzenia”, cloud)
+
+- Package ID: PKG-20260721-events-and-meetings
+- Status: ready
+- Tier: developer
+- Depends on: none
+- Risk: medium (WeekView is stability-sensitive; the change is additive-presentational only)
+- Codex review: required — cross-module (store + storage + cloud + RLS + calendar UI)
+
+## Goal
+
+A new `CalendarEvent` entity (meetings) with reducer CRUD, storage repair,
+cloud mirror + RLS table, presentational blocks in WeekView (+ MonthView
+marker), a slot-menu shortcut „+ Dodaj spotkanie”, and a new panel
+„Wydarzenia” with a URL-driven modal. All user-facing strings Polish.
+
+## Wiki context
+
+- `openwiki/n2hub/state-and-persistence.md`
+- `openwiki/n2hub/scheduling-and-calendar.md`
+- `openwiki/n2hub/cloud-database.md`
+- `openwiki/n2hub/ui-navigation-and-onboarding.md`
+
+## Expected touchpoints
+
+- `src/types.ts` — `CalendarEvent` + `AppData.events`
+- `src/store/AppStore.tsx` — action union, reducer cases, MERGE_CLOUD_ENTITIES
+- `src/store/commandValidation.ts` — event draft validation/normalization
+- `src/store/storage.ts` — `emptyData()`, `coerceArray`, `repairEvents`
+- `src/store/selectors.ts` — `calendarEventsOnDate`
+- `src/components/WeekView.tsx` — EventBlock overlay + slot-menu item (additive only)
+- `src/components/MonthView.tsx` — marker
+- `src/components/EventModal.tsx` (new), `src/pages/EventsPage.tsx` (new)
+- `src/App.tsx`, `src/components/icons.ts`, `src/utils/dirtyRegistry.ts`
+- `src/styles.css`
+- `new: supabase/migrations/20260721190000_events.sql`
+- `src/supabase/cloudMirror.ts`, `src/supabase/plannerData.ts`, `src/supabase/migrations.test.ts`
+- Tests: `new: src/store/eventActions.test.ts`, `new: src/store/eventsStorage.test.ts`,
+  extensions in `cloudMerge.test.ts`, `selectors.test.ts`, `cloudMirror.test.ts`,
+  `plannerData.test.ts`, `migrations.test.ts`
+
+## Invariants
+
+- Invariant 6: every invalid event command returns the SAME state reference.
+- Invariant 7: NO changes to calendar pointer/drag handlers, `packDayBlocks`,
+  collision logic, rendered-column hit-testing or bin lifecycle. Event blocks
+  are additive presentational overlays exactly like `.week-recur-block`
+  (WeekView.tsx:961-1011): no pointer/drag handlers; only click/keyboard opens
+  the event modal.
+- Events NEVER create `WorkloadEntry` rows, never enter totals/overload/
+  collisions (invariant 1 parity with recurrence occurrences).
+- `DATA_VERSION` stays 7 — the collection is ADDITIVE (tickets precedent).
+- A failed save must never report `Zapisano`; no changes to save/conflict flows.
+- Never apply the migration to any remote database — file + tests only.
+- No new npm dependencies. No second recurrence implementation — reuse
+  `src/utils/recurrence.ts` verbatim (no edits to that file).
+
+## Prior decisions (ALL settled — do not reopen)
+
+1. **Permission gate: reuse `tasks.manage`.** The slot context menu already
+   opens only for `canManageTasks` (WeekView.tsx:1022, 1182, 1612); a second
+   item slots in without touching the gate. No new `PermAction`
+   (permissions.ts stays unchanged). EventsPage/EventModal gate create/edit/
+   delete controls with `can('tasks.manage')` + `NO_PERM_TITLE` tooltip; the
+   panel itself is visible to every role (tickets precedent, App.tsx:98-99).
+2. **Attendees: `attendee_ids uuid[]` column on `public.events`** (NOT a join
+   table). Whole-row upsert parity with `draftHoursRow`
+   (cloudMirror.ts:276-292: map local person id via `maps.people` /
+   `cloudProfileIds`, DROP unmappable entries, never null the row) and the
+   `profiles.work_days smallint[]` array precedent. A join table is only used
+   where RLS queries it (task_assignments) — events RLS does not.
+3. **No version bump.** Exact tickets precedent: `emptyData()` gets
+   `events: []`, load path gets `coerceArray(parsedRest.events, defaults.events)`
+   (storage.ts:1448 block) and a `repairEvents` pass wrapped around BOTH load
+   paths exactly where `repairTickets` sits (storage.ts:1070, 1400, 1463).
+4. **Recurrence: reuse `TaskRecurrence` type (types.ts:201-207) and
+   `src/utils/recurrence.ts` as-is.** `CalendarEvent.recurrence?: TaskRecurrence`;
+   anchor = `event.date`. Canonicalize with `normalizeRecurrence(raw, event.date)`
+   on THREE boundaries: reducer (ADD/SAVE_EVENT), `repairEvents`, cloud
+   hydration. Structurally invalid recurrence in a reducer draft → same state
+   reference. NO per-occurrence override UI for events (out of scope; overrides
+   surviving normalization are tolerated, not editable). One-time event = no
+   `recurrence` key („jednorazowo”).
+5. **MonthView: IN scope, marker only** — mirror `month-cell-recur`
+   (MonthView.tsx:69-108, styles.css:2141): a small 📅/dot marker with event
+   titles in `title`/`aria-label`, no blocks, no menu.
+6. **RLS: all four commands open `to authenticated`**
+   (`using (true)` / `with check (true)`), `revoke all ... from anon`, RLS
+   enabled, no FORCE. Justification: the calendar is an org-shared surface and
+   the cloud role mapping `handlowiec → worker` (cloudMirror.ts:44-49) makes
+   any role-restricted write either block handlowiec (who holds `tasks.manage`
+   locally) or require an attendee/creator model the local entity does not
+   carry. Client gate is UX-only per CLAUDE.md. Register
+   `'public.events': ['select', 'insert', 'update', 'delete']` in
+   `EXPECTED_POLICIES` (migrations.test.ts:36-74) and the filename in the list
+   (migrations.test.ts:101-124).
+7. **Realtime: add `public.events` to `supabase_realtime`** with the
+   idempotent do-block from 20260721150000_job_titles.sql:57-65 (events render
+   on the shared calendar — planner-entity parity, unlike tickets).
+8. **Retirement gate / coverage: NO changes** to `src/store/persistGate.ts`
+   (lines 20-50) or `src/supabase/migrationStatus.ts` (buildCoverageReport) —
+   exact tickets parity: a mirrored family absent from `NON_MIRRORED_KEYS`
+   already behaves correctly under the retirement gate.
+9. **Local model has NO createdAt/updatedAt** (prompt shape is canonical). The
+   cloud table has `created_at`/`updated_at` with server defaults + the
+   `app.set_updated_at` trigger (tickets.sql:42-45); `eventRow` OMITS both.
+10. **No activity-log entries and no cascades from project/task deletion** —
+    the collection is standalone (tickets precedent, AppStore.tsx:3524-3527).
+    ONE cascade: `DELETE_PERSON` filters the removed id out of every
+    `attendeeIds` (DELETE_COMPANY style); render also defensively ignores
+    unknown ids.
+11. **No demo events in `seed.ts`** (jobTitles/companies precedent).
+
+## Scope
+
+### 1. Model + reducer (types.ts, AppStore.tsx, commandValidation.ts)
+
+- `CalendarEvent { id, title, description, location, meetingUrl, date,
+  startMinutes, durationMinutes, attendeeIds: string[], recurrence?: TaskRecurrence }`
+  placed after `Ticket` (types.ts:330-341); `events: CalendarEvent[]` in
+  `AppData` after `tickets` (types.ts:403). Strings default `''`.
+- Actions `ADD_EVENT { draft }`, `SAVE_EVENT { eventId, draft }`,
+  `DELETE_EVENT { eventId }` mirroring ticket cases (AppStore.tsx:3528-3586):
+  trim strings, unknown id / invalid draft → same reference.
+- Validation in commandValidation.ts (`isValidEventDraft` +
+  `normalizeEventDraft`, isValidTicketDraft style): title required (non-empty
+  after trim); `date` a valid `yyyy-MM-dd` (utils/dates); `startMinutes` finite
+  integer, 15-grid, 0..1425; `durationMinutes` 15-grid, 15..1440;
+  `startMinutes + durationMinutes <= 1440` (one day); `attendeeIds` an array of
+  strings — dedupe and keep only ids present in `state.people` (normalization,
+  not rejection); `meetingUrl` non-empty ⇒ must pass
+  `normalizeProjectDocumentUrl` (src/utils/projectDocuments.ts — http/https
+  only, store the normalized value; unnormalizable non-empty url ⇒ reject
+  draft). `location`/`description`/`meetingUrl` may all be empty.
+  `recurrence`: absent/null ⇒ no key; otherwise `normalizeRecurrence(raw,
+  draft.date)` — `undefined` result for a PROVIDED rule ⇒ same reference.
+- `MERGE_CLOUD_ENTITIES`: optional `events` in the payload exactly like
+  `tickets` (AppStore.tsx:2602, 2622, 2677-2679, 2717-2719) — absent key
+  leaves the collection untouched (by reference); structurally invalid rows
+  fail-close (same reference); valid merge goes through `reconcileRows`
+  (reference-preserving).
+
+### 2. Storage (storage.ts)
+
+- `emptyData()` → `events: []`; `coerceArray(parsedRest.events, defaults.events)`.
+- `repairEvents` modeled on `repairTickets` (storage.ts:1070+), run at both
+  wrap sites (1400, 1463), idempotent by value: drop rows without `id`/`title`
+  or with an invalid `date`; coerce non-string fields to `''`; snap/reject
+  off-grid minutes fail-closed (drop the row — parity with workload
+  fail-closed rules); dedupe + string-filter `attendeeIds` (KEEP orphaned ids —
+  cloud may know people the local set does not; tickets keep the orphaned
+  reporter); re-canonicalize `recurrence` via `normalizeRecurrence(raw, date)`
+  (invalid ⇒ key removed); normalize `meetingUrl` via
+  `normalizeProjectDocumentUrl` (bad scheme ⇒ `''`). Legacy payload without
+  the key ⇒ `[]`, no echo-write.
+
+### 3. Selector (selectors.ts)
+
+- `calendarEventsOnDate(state, date, personFilter?)` next to
+  `recurrenceOccurrencesForDate` (selectors.ts:357-374), returning
+  `Array<{ event, startMinutes, durationMinutes, isOccurrence }>`:
+  - `date === event.date` → the base event (its own minutes) — emit ONCE even
+    when the rule also matches that day (no double render);
+  - else, with `recurrence`, use `expandOccurrences(event.recurrence,
+    event.date, date, date)` (recurrence.ts:171).
+  - Filter semantics: with an active non-empty `personFilter`, show the event
+    only if some attendee is in the filter; an event with EMPTY `attendeeIds`
+    stays visible (an unaddressed meeting is "everyone's").
+
+### 4. WeekView + MonthView (presentational only)
+
+- `EventBlock` component cloned from `RecurBlock` (WeekView.tsx:961-1011):
+  `position: absolute`, `top = startMinutes/60*HOUR_PX`, height from
+  `durationMinutes`, `role="button"`, `tabIndex=0`, Enter/Space + click open
+  the event modal, `stopPropagation` on click, NO pointer/context lifecycle
+  beyond stopping its own contextmenu (like `.week-recur-block`).
+- Render inside the day column mapping BEFORE `packed.map` alongside the
+  recurrence overlay (WeekView.tsx:1621-1634) so real blocks paint on top
+  (deviation-tested precedent from run 244).
+- `openSlotMenu` gains one guard line for `.week-event-block` next to the
+  `.week-recur-block` guard (WeekView.tsx:1183-1186). NOTHING else in
+  openSlotMenu/pointer paths changes.
+- Slot menu (WeekView.tsx:1968-1991): second `context-menu-item` button
+  „+ Dodaj spotkanie (HH:mm)” (`formatMinutes(slotMenu.startMinutes)`) →
+  opens the event modal in "new" mode prefilled with `slotMenu.date` +
+  `slotMenu.startMinutes` (mirror how `openNewTask` passes prefill,
+  WeekView.tsx:1201-1206), then `setSlotMenu(null)`.
+- New color tokens + classes in styles.css near `.week-recur-block`
+  (styles.css:1867-1898): solid distinct look (different hue family from
+  person/task colors, e.g. a violet `--event-*` token), `.week-event-block`,
+  `.month-cell-event`.
+- MonthView: events marker per decision 5.
+
+### 5. Panel „Wydarzenia” (App.tsx, EventsPage, EventModal)
+
+- Export `CalendarClock` from src/components/icons.ts (curated module).
+- NAV entry `['/wydarzenia', 'Wydarzenia', CalendarClock]` after
+  `'/calendar'` (App.tsx:86-101); route `<Route path="/wydarzenia"
+  element={<EventsPage />} />` (App.tsx:510 area); `<EventModal />` mounted
+  once next to `<TicketModal />` (App.tsx:533).
+- `EventModal` mirrors TicketModal (src/components/TicketModal.tsx:24,30):
+  URL param `wydarzenie` (`?wydarzenie=new` / `?wydarzenie=<id>`),
+  `useOpenEvent()` hook, `.task-modal-*` classes, own dirty scope
+  `'event-modal'` in dirtyRegistry.ts (mirror `'ticket-modal'`). Controlled
+  inputs, Polish labels, required marked ` *`: „Tytuł *”, „Data *”,
+  „Godzina *” (15-min steps), „Czas trwania *” (15-min steps, default 60 min),
+  optional: „Osoby” (attendee multi-select from `state.people`), „Link do
+  spotkania”, „Biuro / lokalizacja”, „Opis”, „Cykliczność” (jednorazowo |
+  weekday chips + optional „do” date, TaskModal „Cykliczność” pattern; the
+  rule's start/duration follow the event's own time fields). Explicit save
+  buttons dispatching ADD_EVENT/SAVE_EVENT; „Usuń” with confirm; live Polish
+  validation message while invalid.
+- `EventsPage`: list sorted by `date` then `startMinutes` (Polish empty state
+  „Brak wydarzeń”), each row opens `?wydarzenie=<id>`; „+ Dodaj wydarzenie”
+  gated by `tasks.manage`; show ⟳/„cykliczne” badge for recurring events.
+
+### 6. Cloud (migration + mirror + hydration)
+
+- `supabase/migrations/20260721190000_events.sql`, header comment + idempotent
+  style copied from 20260720230000_tickets.sql: table `public.events`
+  (`id uuid pk default gen_random_uuid()`, `title text not null` with a
+  1..300 length check, `description text not null default ''`,
+  `location text not null default ''`, `meeting_url text not null default ''`,
+  `event_date date not null`, `start_minutes integer not null` + grid CHECKs
+  (multiple of 15, `0 <= start`, `start + duration <= 1440`),
+  `duration_minutes integer not null` (>=15, multiple of 15),
+  `attendee_ids uuid[] not null default '{}'`, `recurrence jsonb` nullable,
+  `created_at`/`updated_at` + `app.set_updated_at` trigger). RLS + policies +
+  anon revoke + realtime per decisions 6-7. No new SQL functions.
+- `cloudMirror.ts`: `eventRow` after `ticketRow` (cloudMirror.ts:307-333) —
+  UUID id required; `attendee_ids` mapped per decision 2; `recurrence:
+  e.recurrence ?? null`; OMIT created_at/updated_at. Diff block as the tenth
+  family, exact tickets shape (cloudMirror.ts:604-616), Polish label
+  „Wydarzenie …”.
+- `plannerData.ts`: tenth parallel select
+  (`'events'`, `'id, title, description, location, meeting_url, event_date,
+  start_minutes, duration_minutes, attendee_ids, recurrence'`) in
+  `loadPlannerSnapshot` (plannerData.ts:312-347) + error fan-in; hydrate rows:
+  invalid `event_date`/off-grid minutes ⇒ skip with Polish diagnostic;
+  attendees mapped cloud→local via `personOf`, ids outside
+  `cloudProfileIds`/maps dropped; `recurrence` re-canonicalized via
+  `normalizeRecurrence(row.recurrence, date)`; add optional
+  `events?: CalendarEvent[]` to `CloudMergePayload` (plannerData.ts:166-180).
+
+## Out of scope
+
+- Per-occurrence override UI/menu for events; event drag/resize/collisions;
+  attendee availability or overload interplay; notifications/invitations/ICS;
+  MonthView event blocks; changes to `src/utils/recurrence.ts`,
+  `permissions.ts`, `persistGate.ts`, `migrationStatus.ts`; applying the
+  migration to the hosted project; onboarding tours for the new panel.
+
+## Acceptance
+
+- [ ] ADD/SAVE/DELETE_EVENT work; every invalid draft (empty title, bad date,
+      off-grid or over-midnight minutes, bad `meetingUrl` scheme, invalid
+      provided recurrence, unknown eventId) returns the SAME state reference.
+- [ ] `javascript:`/`data:` urls never persist and never render as `href`;
+      schemeless urls normalize to `https://`.
+- [ ] Legacy stored payload without `events` loads as `[]` with no echo-write;
+      malformed rows are repaired/dropped idempotently (second pass no-op).
+- [ ] WeekView shows event blocks at the right top/height, visually distinct
+      from task and recurrence blocks; recurring events appear on occurrence
+      dates with no double block on the anchor date; MonthView shows a marker.
+- [ ] Right-click empty slot (as admin/pm/handlowiec) shows BOTH „+ Dodaj
+      zadanie” and „+ Dodaj spotkanie (HH:mm)”; the latter opens the modal
+      prefilled with that date/time; `pracownik` still gets no menu.
+- [ ] No pointer/drag/hit-testing code path changed (diff review shows
+      WeekView changes are: one guard line, one menu item, overlay render,
+      imports/state for the overlay only).
+- [ ] `/wydarzenia` lists events; `?wydarzenie=new|<id>` opens/close-restores
+      the modal; dirty modal edits arm the navigation guard; all strings Polish.
+- [ ] Migration file passes `migrations.test.ts` (list, RLS conventions,
+      EXPECTED_POLICIES incl. `public.events`); never applied remotely.
+- [ ] Mirror round-trip: local event → `eventRow` → hydrated snapshot →
+      `MERGE_CLOUD_ENTITIES` reproduces the event (ids/attendees/recurrence);
+      merge without `events` key leaves the collection by reference.
+- [ ] `npm test` and `npm run build` green; no new dependencies.
+
